					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">krzysiobal wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I need some kind of advice. My FPGA dev-cart needs M2 signal for clocking internal circuitries, but also for decoding accessess to $6000-$7fff (and also $4000-$5fff as some mappers, eg. mapper 90 uses this).<br />I know there is a delay of tens of nanoseconds between M2 changes and !ROMSEL changes<br /><img src="http://obrazki.elektroda.pl/6457640400_1493340716.png" alt="Image" /><br />so M2 transitions need to be delayed by that time. <br /></div><br />I do not see why it would be required to delay M2. I might be wrong, but if you're decoding circuit for SRAM at $6000-$7FFF for example, using M2 directly should work fine.</div>

